 try/catch usage and imports. Lastly, I’ll double-check for issues like direct reflection or version assertions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering metadata for coverage**\\n\\nI’m pondering the potential condition for the metadata type \\\"IdentityFile\\\" and whether it could enable dynamic access coverage for the active class in native tests. If the metadata conditions are met in the active state, that would be great! I’m also curious if having the metadata after the native tests could help cover `Class#forName` calls and make the dynamic report mark them as true. It sounds like this tracker may only log failed dynamic access, which is a bit unclear, but probably true. Should I reset the build report? Maybe not, but I need to finalize everything with the correct paths.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated the `com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27` coverage patch to address why the prior attempt produced no native dynamic-access coverage.\n\nChanges made:\n- Added native reachability metadata in:\n  - `metadata/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/reachability-metadata.json`\n- Registered the reflective JSch implementation classes needed by the `IdentityFileTest`, including:\n  - `com.jcraft.jsch.jce.TripleDESCBC`\n  - `com.jcraft.jsch.jce.MD5`\n  - `com.jcraft.jsch.jce.SignatureRSA`\n  - `com.jcraft.jsch.jce.SignatureDSA`\n  - Supporting SSH handshake classes needed to reach `IdentityFile.getSignature_rsa(...)` and `IdentityFile.getSignature_dss(...)` under Native Image.\n\nThe previous JVM test run passed, but native execution failed at `JSch.addIdentity(...)` with `ClassNotFoundException: com.jcraft.jsch.jce.TripleDESCBC`, before the active `IdentityFile` call sites could be recorded as covered. The new metadata should allow the native test to proceed into the constructor and signing paths.\n\nPer instruction, I did not run or compile the tests myself.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04b7218707e23e620169f56273dae08193bfd58a8b4ac22f0c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 782, "output": 750, "cacheRead": 80384, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 81916, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777689180995, "responseId": "resp_04b7218707e23e620169f5625e13508193a811bd6d35c2ec08"}}
