 set? This could let the test module compile the library with debug info. However, I should be cautious about duplicating classes on the classpath. My goal is to ensure coverage in reports with line numbers, but I don't want to broaden the scope unnecessarily.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JaCoCo alternatives**\\n\\nI’m wondering if I can include class-level coverage with JaCoCo, but it seems like that’s not the way to go. I might need to adjust the `JSch.setConfig` to set the IdentityFile configurations for test helper classes. However, I notice that call sites still show as Unknown Source, which isn't helpful. If I tried `Class.forName` from the helper test, I’m skeptical that it would work either. Maybe the report isn’t accurately reflecting coverage, but it’s asking for another attempt. Adding a source jar to the JVM might help ensure JaCoCo captures source lines.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java compilation issues**\\n\\nI’m compiling all library sources into the test output. I wonder if there are duplicate classes in Java. While the original jar remains as testImplementation, having duplicates is okay, but I can't compile the same source more than once. I need to check for potential compile errors, especially with Java 25 and the old code that uses `yield`. Also, I should verify if Jsch 0.1.27 sources will compile and whether the essential jzlib is included. Let's list the source files for clarity.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_3uOqXKwuoR4aG83X39x9A14x|fc_04b7218707e23e620169f563582ed4819387f5762f9817a524", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find /home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/main/extracted -type f | sed 's|.*/extracted/||' | sort | head -120 && rg -n \"com\\.jcraft\\.jzlib|jzlib\" /home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/main/extracted", "timeout": 10}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"find /home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/main/extracted -type f | sed 's|.*/extracted/||' | sort | head -120 && rg -n \\\"com\\\\.jcraft\\\\.jzlib|jzlib\\\" /home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/main/extracted\",\"timeout\":10}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 438, "output": 1361, "cacheRead": 97280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 99079, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777689408652, "responseId": "resp_04b7218707e23e620169f563420f648193a1602590cda6ec1f"}}
